WEBVTT

00:11.426 --> 00:15.912
Hey church, it's a joy to be with you right now in the midst of all that is going on in our city.

00:16.453 --> 00:21.039
And if you have a Bible, go ahead and grab it and open up to Romans chapter 15.

00:21.660 --> 00:29.391
We are doing a series right now where we're talking about how we respond to this global pandemic with faith, hope and love.

00:29.411 --> 00:34.258
Now last week we talked about love and this week we're going to talk about hope.

00:34.530 --> 00:35.712
And we need this, right?

00:35.772 --> 00:37.454
Because it's crazy right now.

00:37.494 --> 00:39.256
It feels like the end of the world.

00:39.336 --> 00:42.100
I mean, shelves are empty in the grocery stores.

00:42.380 --> 00:44.323
People are buying guns and ammunition.

00:44.403 --> 00:46.105
They're fighting over toilet paper.

00:46.525 --> 00:51.592
I see people walking around with bandanas over their faces, like, or in a Western movie or something.

00:51.632 --> 00:53.454
Like, it's just crazy.

00:53.494 --> 00:54.335
It's chaos.

00:54.996 --> 00:58.120
But of course, it's not just what's happening out there, right?

00:58.200 --> 00:59.602
This has hit home.

00:59.746 --> 01:01.849
for all of us in different ways.

01:01.949 --> 01:08.720
I've talked with many of you throughout this week and I know that there's a lot of people in our church who are sick and they're scared.

01:08.800 --> 01:10.603
Maybe they have the coronavirus.

01:10.803 --> 01:18.515
I've talked with many people who are worried about their parents or their grandparents or those in their lives who are especially vulnerable.

01:19.096 --> 01:25.746
And now that the city has closed down a lot of businesses, the physical illness has compounded to financial hardship for many.

01:25.986 --> 01:29.850
So I've talked with people in our church who have lost jobs, they've lost work.

01:30.530 --> 01:36.296
A lot of people have lost large amounts of money because of events or plans that they had that were canceled.

01:36.857 --> 01:39.960
Some people are worrying about how they're gonna pay rent at the end of the month.

01:40.540 --> 01:44.544
There are engaged couples who have had to cancel or postpone their weddings.

01:44.564 --> 01:48.728
There's medical professionals who are putting themselves at risk daily.

01:48.748 --> 01:53.673
And so with all of this going on, many people in our city are in despair.

01:53.713 --> 01:54.674
They're wondering,

01:54.882 --> 01:56.303
Is there any hope?

01:57.324 --> 02:02.349
And so into that culture, I want to speak the truth of God's word.

02:02.429 --> 02:06.213
And I want to read to you Romans 15 verse 13.

02:06.253 --> 02:07.795
I'm just going to preach on this one verse.

02:07.815 --> 02:14.982
We'll talk about the context around it, but I want to speak this truth of God's word into the very cultural chaos that we find ourselves in.

02:15.042 --> 02:18.025
I'll read this verse for us and then I'll open this time in prayer.

02:18.585 --> 02:20.367
It's Romans 15 verse 13.

02:20.427 --> 02:20.928
It says this.

02:22.249 --> 02:23.410
May the God of hope

02:23.874 --> 02:31.346
Fill you with all joy and peace and believing so that by the power of the Holy Spirit, you may abound in hope.

02:32.067 --> 02:32.948
This is God's word.

02:33.349 --> 02:34.050
Let's pray together.

02:35.172 --> 02:41.141
God, we pray that you would give us hope in the midst of all of this despair.

02:42.083 --> 02:47.251
We pray that we would have eyes to see how the light shines in the darkness.

02:48.393 --> 02:51.538
God, would you just show us yourself through the preaching of the word?

02:51.938 --> 02:53.280
Would you reveal your character?

02:53.300 --> 02:54.522
Would you show us your heart?

02:54.542 --> 02:57.306
Would you show us your purposes and your plan?

02:57.926 --> 03:00.270
And Lord, give us faith to trust in you.

03:01.131 --> 03:04.356
We pray this in Jesus' name, amen, amen.

03:05.778 --> 03:17.394
All right, well, what I wanna do is I wanna walk through this verse and I wanna be able to show you how the God of hope has given us a message of hope so that we can be a people of hope.

03:18.082 --> 03:21.926
All right, so let's start with the God of hope and think of it like this.

03:22.727 --> 03:27.692
Everyone's looking for hope, but let me ask you, what do you place your hope in?

03:28.513 --> 03:37.743
Is it doctors, is it the government, is it financial security or career success, maybe money, maybe you place your hope and your own ability or even in your health?

03:38.704 --> 03:44.690
Well, none of these are bad in and of themselves, but what do you ultimately place your hope in?

03:45.058 --> 03:50.626
See, all these things I just mentioned, they can change overnight, but God is unchanging.

03:51.087 --> 03:53.750
And that's why God is our only hope.

03:54.331 --> 03:56.995
That's why I want to plead with you in this time.

03:57.435 --> 03:58.237
Look to God.

03:58.737 --> 04:05.427
Whatever you're going through, whatever you're struggling with, whatever you're experiencing, take that to the Lord and look to Him.

04:05.447 --> 04:07.730
He is our hope.

04:08.354 --> 04:10.518
I mean, listen, everything is being canceled.

04:10.538 --> 04:12.963
We don't know what we can depend on anymore.

04:13.023 --> 04:19.075
Events are being canceled, weddings are being canceled, professional sports are being canceled, concerts are being canceled.

04:19.496 --> 04:21.900
All my plans for March and April have been canceled.

04:22.021 --> 04:26.189
All your plans for March and April have been canceled, but let me remind you of this.

04:26.930 --> 04:28.653
God's grace is not canceled.

04:29.235 --> 04:31.058
God's mercy is not canceled.

04:31.202 --> 04:33.325
God's faithfulness is not canceled.

04:33.425 --> 04:35.188
God's goodness is not canceled.

04:35.228 --> 04:37.171
God's love is not canceled.

04:37.211 --> 04:39.234
God's promises are not canceled.

04:39.575 --> 04:42.018
And God's plan is not canceled.

04:42.459 --> 04:44.662
That's why he is our hope.

04:46.005 --> 04:48.248
But we've got to understand what hope is.

04:48.829 --> 04:53.015
Because I think we often use the word differently in our culture than the Bible uses it.

04:53.736 --> 04:57.522
Hope is not naive optimism or wishful thinking.

04:57.602 --> 05:02.409
That's how a lot of people use the word hope today when they say, I hope it doesn't rain tomorrow.

05:02.469 --> 05:08.679
They're saying, I wish, I desire, but the Bible has a different understanding of hope.

05:09.300 --> 05:13.286
Biblical hope is not naive optimism or wishful thinking.

05:13.827 --> 05:21.138
It is an unflinching confidence in God's power to accomplish God's purposes in God's timing.

05:21.698 --> 05:28.947
It's the refusal to despair because no matter how bad it looks, we remember how good God is.

05:29.949 --> 05:38.319
And so in everything that's going on in your life and in this world, you can have an assurance that because of God, you are loved.

05:38.780 --> 05:43.626
You are not alone and you will always be secure in his grip.

05:43.646 --> 05:46.610
I mean, everything in this world is being shaken right now.

05:47.106 --> 05:50.470
It feels like everything in our city is being shaken in your lives.

05:50.530 --> 05:52.853
It feels like everything is being shaken up.

05:53.314 --> 05:56.418
But remember that we are a part of a kingdom that is unshakeable.

05:57.059 --> 06:01.624
If you have trusted in Christ, then you have a firm foundation.

06:02.105 --> 06:09.034
And you can have this kind of unflinching confidence, not because it's rooted in you, but because it's rooted in God.

06:09.394 --> 06:10.956
He's the God of hope.

06:11.957 --> 06:15.602
And so this God of hope then gives us a message of hope.

06:15.906 --> 06:18.690
Look at Romans 15, 13, once more.

06:18.730 --> 06:25.319
It says, may the God of hope fill you with all joy and peace in believing.

06:26.220 --> 06:31.207
Now, when he says you here, he's speaking to a church in Italy.

06:31.928 --> 06:36.113
God wrote a letter to a church in Italy in the city of Rome.

06:36.133 --> 06:41.701
They were probably gathering in houses just like you and I, but without internet and air conditioning.

06:42.542 --> 06:45.426
But as they gathered in Rome, you need to understand that

06:45.698 --> 06:47.921
This was a brutal place for Christians.

06:48.662 --> 06:55.933
They were living in a pagan environment, ridden by plagues, where there was much persecution against followers of Jesus.

06:56.814 --> 07:04.965
And into that difficult space, the apostle Paul says to them, may the God of hope fill you with all joy and peace.

07:05.786 --> 07:10.834
They can have joy and peace, even in those circumstances, and not just joy and peace.

07:11.174 --> 07:13.938
He says, all joy and peace.

07:14.466 --> 07:19.771
We should remember that Psalm 16 says in God's presence is the fullness of joy.

07:20.372 --> 07:24.336
Philippians 4 talks about a peace that surpasses understanding.

07:25.117 --> 07:26.938
And it's not just joy and peace.

07:26.998 --> 07:30.442
It appears that hope then is a byproduct of these.

07:31.203 --> 07:42.674
So if you think about what it says in verse 13 there, he says, the God of hopefully with all joy and peace and believing so that by the power of the Holy Spirit, you may abound in hope.

07:43.650 --> 07:53.646
And so the joy and the peace that are a result of what God has done for you will increase your hope in what he will do for you.

07:54.628 --> 08:04.103
But this joy and peace and hope, they all come as a result of what God has done for us by his grace in sending his son Jesus.

08:04.864 --> 08:08.089
And that's clear in the verses leading up to verse 13.

08:08.169 --> 08:11.154
This isn't just a generic message of hope.

08:11.490 --> 08:14.213
No, it's hope that we have in Christ.

08:14.954 --> 08:29.332
In verse eight, it talks about how Christ the king, our king became a servant to fulfill all of God's promises of salvation and to bring mercy to the nations as a display of the glory of God.

08:30.113 --> 08:40.306
And I want you to understand there when it talks about the nations, that the nations there, it mentions Gentiles in there, but it literally means nations, nations like China,

08:40.770 --> 08:45.418
like Italy, like Germany, like Iran, like the United States.

08:46.180 --> 08:51.088
Christ came to bring joy and peace and hope to the nations.

08:51.689 --> 09:00.865
And so this king who came as a servant then goes on in Romans 15 and it mentions four Old Testament promises fulfilled in Christ.

09:01.306 --> 09:05.714
It's showing how it's this incredible story of God renewing his creation

09:05.826 --> 09:08.189
And it culminates in Christ the king.

09:08.530 --> 09:17.682
And the fourth of these Old Testament promises is one from Isaiah chapter 11 that says, in him, the Gentiles or the nations have hope.

09:18.683 --> 09:23.430
And so listen, we don't get our hope and peace from the news headlines.

09:23.910 --> 09:28.536
We get our hope and peace from God and the good news that he has sent his son.

09:29.197 --> 09:32.722
Christ died on the cross for your sins.

09:32.962 --> 09:36.427
and he rose from the grave so that you might have life.

09:37.068 --> 09:39.051
This is the good news of God's grace.

09:39.751 --> 09:42.716
He took our shame and we receive joy.

09:42.776 --> 09:45.600
He took our pain and we receive peace.

09:45.980 --> 09:48.824
He took our sin and we receive salvation.

09:49.625 --> 09:54.853
Christ entered into our hopeless world so that our world can have hope in him.

09:54.893 --> 09:58.738
But you need to understand that this good news of the gospel

09:58.914 --> 10:02.898
of salvation, of new life, of peace, of joy in Christ.

10:03.779 --> 10:04.840
It's received through faith.

10:05.681 --> 10:11.247
That's why it talks about in verse 13, the joy and peace in believing.

10:12.208 --> 10:15.812
And this faith is a trust in God.

10:16.513 --> 10:18.335
It's a trust in God's promises.

10:19.076 --> 10:20.958
It's a trust in God's character.

10:21.619 --> 10:23.020
It's a trust that he is our hope.

10:24.322 --> 10:28.306
To have faith means that when we look around in our circumstances,

10:28.642 --> 10:36.773
and it doesn't feel like, or it doesn't seem like God is good, that we trust that God is good, that we trust that God is faithful.

10:37.515 --> 10:45.506
When we look around in our circumstances and we wonder what God is up to, we remember God's promises, I will never leave you nor forsake you.

10:46.287 --> 10:48.330
I will accomplish all of my purposes.

10:49.331 --> 10:51.234
I'm renewing heaven and earth.

10:52.416 --> 10:55.199
Faith is as trusting in God's promises.

10:56.021 --> 10:57.042
That often means

10:57.154 --> 11:06.585
not trusting in our own doubts, even in our own feelings, where we wonder what's going on, but we keep our eyes fixed on Christ.

11:06.686 --> 11:10.690
It's not the quality of your faith that matters so much.

11:10.771 --> 11:14.275
It's the object of your faith, and that is Christ.

11:14.856 --> 11:20.282
And I want to call all of us to trusting the Lord in the midst of this time, where that's difficult.

11:21.243 --> 11:26.770
Many of you are Christians and you've been a part of our church for a long time,

11:26.978 --> 11:31.465
And as everything's being shaken up, your commitment has just shined through in all of this.

11:31.545 --> 11:37.194
It's been so encouraging to see the church gather together and find creative ways of loving one another.

11:37.275 --> 11:42.383
And so I just want to say to you as a church that your faith has shown.

11:42.423 --> 11:46.770
It's evident to me, to our pastors, it's evident to the city.

11:47.731 --> 11:48.593
And I'm proud of you.

11:48.833 --> 11:51.277
I'm really grateful for our church in the midst of all of this.

11:51.898 --> 11:54.322
But I also know that many are watching this right now.

11:54.722 --> 11:55.703
who don't know Jesus.

11:56.024 --> 11:56.965
They're not Christians.

11:57.566 --> 12:00.871
And in the midst of this tragedy, they're looking for hope.

12:01.492 --> 12:06.139
They're wondering what they can stand on as everything else is changing.

12:06.660 --> 12:19.558
And so if that's you, if you're listening to this today, whether a friend invited you to a digital gathering or whether someone sent this to you or you stumbled across it online, whatever that is, I want you to hear that there is hope.

12:20.059 --> 12:22.002
There is hope in Christ.

12:22.274 --> 12:28.564
You were made for this to know God and love God and be known by God and be loved by God.

12:28.944 --> 12:32.330
So put your hope in Jesus today and live for him.

12:32.370 --> 12:40.582
There's peace and joy and hope even in times where everything is out of order and it's hard to know what's gonna happen next.

12:40.943 --> 12:42.225
We know who God is.

12:42.586 --> 12:45.811
We know his heart for us because he sent his son, Jesus.

12:46.952 --> 12:50.578
So what we see in Romans 15, 13 is that we see a God of hope

12:50.914 --> 12:55.681
who gives us a message of hope so that we can be a people of hope.

12:56.602 --> 13:05.694
Now, I want you to notice here when it says in verse 13, so that by the power of the Holy Spirit, you may abound in hope.

13:06.375 --> 13:10.841
I want you to notice that the you there in the original language of Greek, it's plural.

13:11.823 --> 13:14.006
Paul is not saying this to individuals.

13:14.326 --> 13:16.229
He's writing this to a community.

13:16.269 --> 13:19.954
This is a letter that's written to the church in Rome.

13:20.450 --> 13:23.493
And so he's talking to them together in this.

13:25.195 --> 13:33.204
What they need to have the hope that they long for is they need God, but they also need each other in the midst of all of this.

13:33.724 --> 13:39.430
Their abounding in hope is intricately woven to the depth of their relationships.

13:40.391 --> 13:42.734
And you see this in the context.

13:43.054 --> 13:47.940
Look in your Bibles at verses five and seven in Romans 15, just up ahead.

13:48.440 --> 13:50.162
And it says this, Paul says to them,

13:50.754 --> 14:04.996
May the God of endurance and encouragement grant you to live in such harmony with one another in accord with Christ Jesus that together you may with one voice glorify the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ.

14:05.497 --> 14:11.025
Therefore welcome one another as Christ has welcomed you for the glory of God.

14:12.067 --> 14:19.378
So this is a command by God for us and it's gonna look different when we have social distancing and all of that

14:19.586 --> 14:29.938
But we have to find creative ways to be able to do this, to endure, to encourage one another, to be at harmony with one another in accord with Christ Jesus.

14:30.638 --> 14:39.488
Remember that in all of this, that the unity that we have, it's not in our ability to rally, it's not even in our beliefs, it's in Christ.

14:39.949 --> 14:41.971
He is our unity.

14:42.712 --> 14:48.178
And so I wanna call you to be community, to be the church in the midst of all of this.

14:48.258 --> 14:53.004
Don't let physical separation mean relational isolation.

14:53.665 --> 14:57.050
This is a time more than ever to bind together.

14:57.090 --> 15:02.777
And that includes showing love and compassion, especially to those who are hurting right now.

15:03.558 --> 15:08.625
A lot of people are hurting, they're struggling, and we're called to be a people of hope and peace.

15:09.226 --> 15:13.812
But we also share in one another sorrow and bear each other's burdens.

15:14.813 --> 15:15.634
We grieve.

15:15.810 --> 15:17.752
And there's a lot to grieve right now.

15:17.792 --> 15:18.793
There's a lot of loss.

15:18.873 --> 15:20.855
People are experiencing loss.

15:20.895 --> 15:27.862
But remember when it says in 1 Thessalonians 4, we grieve, but we do not grieve as those without hope.

15:29.604 --> 15:37.171
We need to remember that this social distancing cannot keep us from the relationships that we were made for.

15:37.551 --> 15:39.193
We've got to strive for unity.

15:39.614 --> 15:44.178
We've got to build one another up in faith, in love, and in hope.

15:44.546 --> 15:48.092
Because even in our suffering, we can abound in hope.

15:49.173 --> 15:50.616
Don't you love that it says that in here?

15:50.636 --> 15:54.021
It doesn't just say that God's people may have hope.

15:54.602 --> 15:57.627
It says so that they may abound in hope.

15:58.308 --> 16:02.294
And that's because we have a God of hope and God's not short on hope.

16:02.975 --> 16:04.257
It's not like God is in heaven.

16:04.377 --> 16:07.623
He's just got a drop here or there to give to us.

16:07.703 --> 16:09.285
No, it's a downpour.

16:09.746 --> 16:12.370
It's a flood of hope from the Lord.

16:12.834 --> 16:15.978
And we are filled with God's hope, but it doesn't stay in us.

16:16.619 --> 16:21.384
It spills over so that we're a people of hope to others.

16:22.085 --> 16:25.750
And remember, we're literally talking about a supernatural hope.

16:26.731 --> 16:32.017
This is not just some virtue that you need to muster up or that you need to try to have more hope in your life.

16:32.678 --> 16:38.685
This is the power of the Holy Spirit making this hope abound in you.

16:38.705 --> 16:42.450
And I think a biblical understanding of hope

16:43.074 --> 16:44.977
is going to be an active hope.

16:45.918 --> 16:51.105
It's not just sitting back and doing nothing and kind of wishing that God would do something.

16:51.185 --> 16:52.307
No, it's an active hope.

16:52.367 --> 16:57.694
And I want to acknowledge that that's going to look different for people in different situations right now in our city.

16:58.255 --> 16:59.476
Some of you are quarantined.

17:00.057 --> 17:04.243
And I want to say in the midst of that, don't waste the time that you have.

17:05.004 --> 17:09.370
There's a difference between doing nothing and waiting patiently on the Lord.

17:10.211 --> 17:12.434
Now take advantage of this time for prayer.

17:12.706 --> 17:24.922
for solitude, to read scripture, to read good books, to connect with other people through digital mediums, don't waste the time that you have, have an active hope.

17:25.663 --> 17:30.589
But I also want to acknowledge that for some of you, your hope is very different, that you're not quarantined.

17:30.629 --> 17:31.691
In fact, it's the opposite.

17:32.172 --> 17:35.175
In many ways, you're working tirelessly right now.

17:35.736 --> 17:37.138
For many of you, because of

17:37.602 --> 17:45.970
whether it's your job and what that requires of you or you have kids at home now throughout the day where you haven't had that and you're scrambling trying to figure it out.

17:45.990 --> 17:49.213
I want to call you to hope in the Lord.

17:49.994 --> 17:55.259
And as we talk about hope, I look around and there's a lot of hardship.

17:55.279 --> 17:56.140
There's a lot of trials.

17:56.160 --> 17:57.301
There's a lot of difficulty.

17:57.842 --> 17:59.303
But I see that hope is rising.

18:00.084 --> 18:06.450
I see people having hope in people in our church being a people of hope and the Lord working through them.

18:06.626 --> 18:07.868
in little ways.

18:07.968 --> 18:17.522
I mean, this last week I heard stories of people meeting the elderly people that are around them for the first time in their lives, neighbors or people in their apartment buildings.

18:17.582 --> 18:22.088
I've heard of people in apartment buildings taking care of each other for the first time.

18:22.108 --> 18:28.557
I've heard of people in our church buying toilet paper and driving it around and giving it to anyone that they needed have that.

18:28.577 --> 18:28.978
There's

18:29.154 --> 18:32.859
The good stuff of life goes on in the midst of this.

18:32.899 --> 18:34.901
There were babies that were born this week.

18:34.941 --> 18:38.045
There were couples that got married this week.

18:38.065 --> 18:42.431
There's so much good that's going on that gives us reason for hope.

18:42.951 --> 18:49.600
I mean, right now, I'm filming this in our office, which is right next to the Hope Center.

18:50.361 --> 18:57.970
And the Hope Center is a space where I've heard person after person describe

18:58.114 --> 19:03.583
The first time they came there is saying, I came here hopeless, having no hope.

19:04.384 --> 19:09.873
And yet, people being able to say, but God did a work in my life that's turned me around.

19:10.574 --> 19:21.733
And whether that's people getting off the streets or recovering from addiction or meeting the Lord or finding community and family for the first time, God is doing incredible works there.

19:21.773 --> 19:22.975
We're getting to see it firsthand.

19:23.015 --> 19:24.978
And I want you to know that because

19:25.218 --> 19:33.427
What we need to do to be faithful in the midst of all of this is to stay home, to be careful, to practice social distancing, all of that.

19:34.008 --> 19:39.154
But I also want you to know that we as a church are still serving this city in so many ways.

19:39.615 --> 19:47.844
We've had to be really careful with the food ministry and we've made a lot of adjustments to make sure it's safe, healthy protocols and all of that.

19:47.884 --> 19:51.188
We're giving away to go boxes, but we're still feeding the hungry.

19:51.408 --> 19:53.010
Who else is going to feed them?

19:53.410 --> 19:55.653
We're still loving the city in every way that we can.

19:55.693 --> 20:02.723
So we would ask that you continue to pray and support however you can in that knowing that the Lord is doing a good work.

20:03.604 --> 20:05.567
So I'm honestly excited in all this.

20:05.627 --> 20:16.802
I believe that the Lord is at work, but I also want to say to you, I want to acknowledge as your pastor that there's a temptation for me and for others to say, well, it will be okay.

20:17.483 --> 20:18.504
It'll all be fine.

20:18.544 --> 20:19.866
It's almost over.

20:19.926 --> 20:22.610
It's probably not going to get any worse.

20:23.010 --> 20:24.612
But listen, we don't know that.

20:25.713 --> 20:28.235
It might get better, it could get much worse.

20:29.216 --> 20:38.385
And what I want for you is I want you to have a hope that can handle either one of those, whether it gets better or whether it gets worse.

20:38.885 --> 20:49.655
You see this in Psalm 73, the attitude of the Psalmist, he says, first in verse 25, he says, who have I in heaven but you?

20:49.695 --> 20:52.498
And there is nothing on earth that I desire besides you.

20:52.994 --> 20:54.676
He's saying, God is my help.

20:55.498 --> 20:57.400
God is who I ultimately look to.

20:58.822 --> 21:06.172
But it's only when you have that kind of faith in God, like we see in verse 25, that then you can say what he says in verse 26.

21:06.253 --> 21:12.922
He says, my flesh and my heart may fail, but God is the strength of my heart and my portion forever.

21:13.863 --> 21:16.948
He's saying, I trust in God, I have faith in God.

21:17.088 --> 21:18.850
I believe that God can do anything.

21:19.291 --> 21:21.554
But even if my health fails,

21:22.306 --> 21:26.452
Even if things don't work out the way that I want, I trust in God.

21:26.792 --> 21:28.114
He is my hope.

21:28.555 --> 21:38.088
That's the kind of hope that you can have, this unflinching confidence in God, knowing that he is with you and knowing that he is for you.

21:38.929 --> 21:44.277
Now, I started off talking about how it feels like a strange apocalyptic time.

21:44.377 --> 21:45.879
It feels like the end of the world.

21:45.959 --> 21:50.866
Well, the Bible, of course, talks about the end of the world and it gives us hope.

21:51.234 --> 21:54.178
not just for the end of the world, but for eternity.

21:54.799 --> 22:07.397
And in Revelation 21, you have this beautiful picture of Christ enthroned over all of creation, saying, behold, I am making all things new.

22:08.318 --> 22:17.531
I want to call you to look to Christ the King and put your hope in here, knowing that one day, because of God's grace, every disease will be healed.

22:18.072 --> 22:19.474
Every wound will be bound up.

22:19.842 --> 22:21.824
Every tear will be wiped away.

22:22.285 --> 22:23.926
All evil will be banished.

22:24.127 --> 22:28.131
Sin will be forgiven and creation will be made new.

22:28.151 --> 22:34.357
In Christ, your future is guaranteed and it's better than you could ever imagine.

22:34.878 --> 22:39.663
So may we put our faith in Him, our hope and our salvation.

22:40.123 --> 22:40.844
Let's pray together.

22:42.226 --> 22:46.290
God, we thank you that you are our hope.

22:47.170 --> 22:57.303
that when we look to the things in our lives around us and they're failing, they're falling apart, they're letting us down, we can look to you and know that you are unfailing.

22:57.963 --> 22:58.925
You are faithful.

22:59.465 --> 23:00.947
You are at work in all of this.

23:01.828 --> 23:04.151
God, we remember that you are a refuge.

23:04.932 --> 23:10.239
You are a strong tower that we can run to for shelter in times of danger.

23:10.259 --> 23:13.002
And so Lord, we look to you in all of this.

23:13.723 --> 23:16.146
God, I pray that you would increase our faith

23:16.674 --> 23:18.397
May we trust in you during this time.

23:18.497 --> 23:33.281
We pray that you would teach us to love one another well, to support one another, to show your grace and your mercy to this city in ways that are wise and faithful and show your heart for the city, ultimately, Lord.

23:34.163 --> 23:37.728
We love you and we love because you first loved us.

23:37.828 --> 23:41.234
And so we give you all the glory in Jesus' name, amen.

